# Ntoky — Senior Full-Stack Developer, Johannesburg (SAST / UTC+2)

## Project Identity
This is "The Record" — a South African legal intelligence and news timeline platform.
It tracks real-world stories from incident → charges → court → outcome.
It maps events to the South African Constitution, statutes (PRECCA, SAPS Act, etc.), and case law.
It must explain legal concepts in plain English understandable to a child.

## Human Impact Layer
The /impact page is the most emotionally significant page on the platform.
It answers: "What does all of this actually mean for ordinary South Africans?"

Eight sectors, each linked to a constitutional right:
  housing (Section 26), water (Section 27), health (Section 27),
  education (Section 29), jobs (Section 22), safety (Section 12),
  food (Section 27), transport (implied Section 9 equality framing).

Key entities:
  ImpactSector (8 rows — reference table, rarely edited)
  StoryImpactSector (join: story + sector + impact_chain JSON/array)
  ExpenditureImpactSector (join: expenditure + sector + what_was_not_built)
  CommissionImpactSector (join: commission + sector)

The impact_chain is the most important narrative field in this layer.
It is an ordered text array showing HOW money stolen in one place
reaches the life of an ordinary person elsewhere.
Seed it from the perspective of the affected person,
ending with a human consequence:
  WRONG last step: 'Audit finding issued'
  RIGHT last step: 'Child misses school because the roof is leaking'

what_it_should_have_funded is the most shareable field on expenditure rows.
Compute illustrative equivalents using these editorial constants:
  RDP house: R250,000
  School repair (full): R5,000,000
  Water connection (household): R50,000
  Child Support Grant (1 year): R6,360 (R530 × 12)
  Old Age Grant (1 year): R26,400 (R2,200 × 12)
  ICU hospital bed: R1,000,000
  Teacher salary (1 year): R300,000

MoneyToReality endpoint: GET /api/impact/money-to-reality?rands=N
Returns floored counts for each conversion.

Public API routes:
  GET /api/impact/sectors
  GET /api/impact/sectors/:slug
  GET /api/impact/web
  GET /api/impact/story/:storyId
  GET /api/impact/money-to-reality?rands=N

Web routes:
  /impact — spider-web human cost page (force-dynamic, error.tsx)

Navigation:
  Desktop Header: "Impact" before "About"
  Mobile nav: "The Real Cost" subtitle "How corruption affects you" → /impact

Presentation rules:
  Spider-web SVG: draw radial spokes first (pathLength), then fade sector nodes.
  Never show the spider-web block without constitutional-rights framing nearby.
  Always show plain_english_child per sector (PlainEnglishBox child level).
  Disclaimer on impact stats:
    "These figures show the scale of service delivery failures.
     Not all are caused solely by corruption — but all are worsened by it."

