## Cursor Behaviour
- When asked to create a file, create the complete file. No placeholders.
- When asked to scaffold a module, create all files in the module (controller, service, module, dto).
- When writing Tailwind, always think mobile-first: base styles for mobile, md: for tablet, lg: for desktop.
- When writing animations, use Framer Motion variants with staggerChildren.
- Always add db indexes on foreign keys and frequently queried columns.
- When writing Python, always use async def and await for IO operations.


## DEPLOYMENT — READ BEFORE ANY CHANGE

### Critical facts that break deployments if ignored

1. PRODUCTION CONTAINER HAS NO SOURCE FILES
   The API container only has dist/ (compiled JS).
   Never reference src/ paths in production commands.
   Migration runner: /repo/apps/api/dist/database/run-migrations.js
   Seeds: /repo/apps/api/dist/database/seeds/index.js

2. DATABASE_URL MUST BE IN .env
   File: /opt/therecord/app/.env
   Format: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://therecord:PASSWORD@therecord-postgres:5432/therecord
   The # in the password must be URL-encoded as %23
   The container reads .env ONLY at creation time.
   docker restart does NOT reload .env.
   To apply .env changes: docker compose down && docker compose up -d

3. DOCKER COMPOSE SERVICE NAMES
   In docker-compose.yml services are named:
     api, web, intelligence, postgres
   Container names at runtime:
     therecord-api, therecord-web,
     therecord-intelligence, therecord-postgres
   Use service names with compose commands.
   Use container names with docker exec.

4. NETWORK
   Network name: therecord-network
   Was created manually — has no compose labels.
   If compose recreates it, containers can communicate.
   Internal hostnames: therecord-postgres, therecord-api etc.

5. MIGRATION RUNNER
   DO NOT use: npm run migration:run
     (requires TypeScript source — not in prod image)
   DO use: docker exec therecord-api
     node /repo/apps/api/dist/database/run-migrations.js
   Must pass DATABASE_URL via --env-file or container env.

6. SEEDS
   Run ONCE on fresh database only.
   Safe to re-run (all upserts).
   Command:
     docker exec --env-file /tmp/seed.env therecord-api
     node /repo/apps/api/dist/database/seeds/index.js
   Order is fixed in index.js:
     commissions → adhoc → siu → mkhwanazi

7. PASSWORD SPECIAL CHARACTERS
   POSTGRES_PASSWORD=Tr3c0rd#Hetzner2026!
   The # breaks bash and URL parsing.
   In .env file: write as-is (Tr3c0rd#Hetzner2026!)
   In DATABASE_URL: encode # as %23
   In bash commands: use python3 -c or heredoc with 'EOF'
   Never use double quotes around passwords in bash.

8. NEXT.JS PAGES MUST BE force-dynamic
   All pages that fetch API data must have:
     export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'
   Without this, next build tries to prerender
   at build time when API is not running → build fails.

9. SPACY VERSION
   Pin to: spacy==3.7.4
   Version 3.7.6 is yanked from PyPI.
   File: apps/intelligence/requirements.txt

10. DOMAIN
    Production: https://therecord.co.za
    OLD (retired): therecord.codist.co.za
    Never use the old domain in any file.
    metadataBase in layout.tsx: https://therecord.co.za
    CORS in api/src/main.ts: https://therecord.co.za

