### Deploy script order
  1. git pull
  2. docker compose up -d --build
  3. sleep 20
  4. docker exec therecord-api node
     /repo/apps/api/dist/database/run-migrations.js
  5. docker image prune -f

### Common failure modes and fixes

FAILURE: 502 Bad Gateway
  CAUSE: API container not running or
         DATABASE_URL not set
  FIX: docker compose down && up -d
       Check .env has DATABASE_URL

FAILURE: relation "X" does not exist
  CAUSE: Migrations not run
  FIX: Run run-migrations.js

FAILURE: DATABASE_URL is not set
  CAUSE: Container created without .env
         OR docker restart used instead of
         docker compose down/up
  FIX: docker compose down && up -d

FAILURE: next build fails on /laws page
  CAUSE: Page missing force-dynamic export
  FIX: Add export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'

FAILURE: seed fails — Law "X" not found
  CAUSE: Seed running before migrations
         OR law missing from seed data
  FIX: Run migrations first, then seeds

FAILURE: nginx reload fails
  CAUSE: Another site config has bad SSL cert
  FIX: Check /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/ for
       stale configs, remove broken symlinks

FAILURE: deploy script syntax error
  CAUSE: bash -c with single quotes or
         special chars in password
  FIX: Use simple sequential commands,
       no subshells, no bash -c '...'